&lt;p&gt;Summary&lt;br/&gt;
-------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unwraps RemoteExceptions and we don&apos;t abort if it&apos;s an NSRE.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This handling is rather different from the handling of opens (we abort in some cases here), so we might consider making them the same and no longer aborting here.  I&apos;m fine with leaving it for a while longer as we do all this testing.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This addresses bug &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3163&quot; title=&quot;If we timeout PENDING_CLOSE and send another closeRegion RPC, need to handle NSRE from RS (comes as a RemoteException)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3163&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3163&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
